00884 /* Copy to YYRES the contents of YYSTR after stripping away unnecessary
00885    quotes and backslashes, so that it's suitable for yyerror.  The
00886    heuristic is that double-quoting is unnecessary unless the string
00887    contains an apostrophe, a comma, or backslash (other than

00892 yytnamerr (char *yyres, const char *yystr)
00893 {
00894   if (*yystr == '"')
00895     {
00896       YYSIZE_T yyn = 0;
00897       char const *yyp = yystr;
00898 
00899       for (;;)
00900         switch (*++yyp)
00901           {
00902           case '\'':
00903           case ',':
00904             goto do_not_strip_quotes;
00905

01102 /*----------.
01103 | yyparse.  |
01104 `----------*/
01105 
01106 #ifdef YYPARSE_PARAM
01107 #if (defined __STDC__ || defined __C99__FUNC__ \
01108      || defined __cplusplus || defined _MSC_VER)
01109 int
01110 yyparse (void *YYPARSE_PARAM)
01111 #else
01112 int
01113 yyparse (YYPARSE_PARAM)
01114     void *YYPARSE_PARAM;
01115 #endif
01116 #else /* ! YYPARSE_PARAM */
01117 #if (defined __STDC__ || defined __C99__FUNC__ \
01118      || defined __cplusplus || defined _MSC_VER)
01119 int
01120 yyparse (void)
01121 #else
01122 int
01123 yyparse ()
01124 
01125 #endif
01126 #endif
01127 {
01128   
01129   int yystate;
01130   int yyn;
01131   int yyresult;
01132   /* Number of tokens to shift before error messages enabled.  */
01133   int yyerrstatus;
01134   /* Look-ahead token as an internal (translated) token number.  */
01135   int yytoken = 0;
01136 #if YYERROR_VERBOSE
01137   /* Buffer for error messages, and its allocated size.  */
01138   char yymsgbuf[128];
01139   char *yymsg = yymsgbuf;
01140   YYSIZE_T yymsg_alloc = sizeof yymsgbuf;
01141 #endif
01142 
01143   /* Three stacks and their tools:
01144      `yyss': related to states,
01145      `yyvs': related to semantic values,
01146      `yyls': related to locations.
01147 
01148      Refer to the stacks thru separate pointers, to allow yyoverflow
01149      to reallocate them elsewhere.  */
01150 
01151   /* The state stack.  */
01152   yytype_int16 yyssa[YYINITDEPTH];
01153   yytype_int16 *yyss = yyssa;
01154   yytype_int16 *yyssp;
01155 
01156   /* The semantic value stack.  */
01157   YYSTYPE yyvsa[YYINITDEPTH];
01158   YYSTYPE *yyvs = yyvsa;
01159   YYSTYPE *yyvsp;
01160 
01161 
01162 
01163 #define YYPOPSTACK(N)   (yyvsp -= (N), yyssp -= (N))
01164 
01165   YYSIZE_T yystacksize = YYINITDEPTH;
01166 
01167   /* The variables used to return semantic value and location from the
01168      action routines.  */
01169   YYSTYPE yyval;
01170 
01171 
01172   /* The number of symbols on the RHS of the reduced rule.
01173      Keep to zero when no symbol should be popped.  */
01174   int yylen = 0;
01175 
01176   YYDPRINTF ((stderr, "Starting parse\n"));
01177 
01178   yystate = 0;
01179   yyerrstatus = 0;
01180   yynerrs = 0;
01181   yychar = YYEMPTY;             /* Cause a token to be read.  */
01182 
01183   /* Initialize stack pointers.
01184      Waste one element of value and location stack
01185      so that they stay on the same level as the state stack.
01186      The wasted elements are never initialized.  */
01187 
01188   yyssp = yyss;
01189   yyvsp = yyvs;
01190 
01191   goto yysetstate;
01192 
01193 /*------------------------------------------------------------.
01194 | yynewstate -- Push a new state, which is found in yystate.  |
01195 `------------------------------------------------------------*/
01196  yynewstate:
01197   /* In all cases, when you get here, the value and location stacks
01198      have just been pushed.  So pushing a state here evens the stacks.  */
01199   yyssp++;
01200 
01201  yysetstate:
01202   *yyssp = yystate;
01203 
01204   if (yyss + yystacksize - 1 <= yyssp)
01205     {
01206       /* Get the current used size of the three stacks, in elements.  */
01207       YYSIZE_T yysize = yyssp - yyss + 1;
01208 
01209 #ifdef yyoverflow
01210       {
01211         /* Give user a chance to reallocate the stack.  Use copies of
01212            these so that the &'s don't force the real ones into
01213            memory.  */
01214         YYSTYPE *yyvs1 = yyvs;
01215         yytype_int16 *yyss1 = yyss;
01216 
01217 
01218         /* Each stack pointer address is followed by the size of the
01219            data in use in that stack, in bytes.  This used to be a
01220            conditional around just the two extra args, but that might
01221            be undefined if yyoverflow is a macro.  */
01222         yyoverflow (YY_("memory exhausted"),
01223                     &yyss1, yysize * sizeof (*yyssp),
01224                     &yyvs1, yysize * sizeof (*yyvsp),
01225 
01226                     &yystacksize);
01227 
01228         yyss = yyss1;
01229         yyvs = yyvs1;
01230       }
01231 #else /* no yyoverflow */
01232 # ifndef YYSTACK_RELOCATE
01233       goto yyexhaustedlab;
01234 # else
01235       /* Extend the stack our own way.  */
01236       if (YYMAXDEPTH <= yystacksize)
01237         goto yyexhaustedlab;
01238       yystacksize *= 2;
01239       if (YYMAXDEPTH < yystacksize)
01240         yystacksize = YYMAXDEPTH;
01241 
01242       {
